```

### Supabase Tables

| Table | Key Columns |
|---|---|
| `devices` | `id`, `name`, `type`, `is_on`, `power_rating`, `brightness/speed/temp`, `usage_duration`, `updated_at` |
| `activity_logs` | `id`, `device_id`, `action`, `timestamp`, `details` |
| `alerts` | `id`, `type`, `message`, `severity`, `is_resolved`, `created_at` |
| `modes` | `id`, `name`, `is_active`, `device_actions` (JSONB) |
| `energy_snapshots` | `id`, `total_watts`, `per_device` (JSONB), `recorded_at` |

---

## 7. API Endpoints (Suggested)

| Method | Endpoint | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `GET` | `/api/devices` | List all devices with current state |
| `POST` | `/api/devices/{id}/toggle` | Turn device ON/OFF |
| `POST` | `/api/devices/{id}/action` | Perform device-specific action (e.g., set brightness) |
| `GET` | `/api/energy` | Get current total and per-device consumption |
| `GET` | `/api/energy/history` | Historical energy snapshots |
| `POST` | `/api/modes/activate` | Activate a specific automation mode |
| `GET` | `/api/modes` | List modes and their statuses |
| `GET` | `/api/logs` | Retrieve activity logs (paginated, filterable) |
| `GET` | `/api/alerts` | List active alerts |
| `POST` | `/api/alerts/{id}/resolve` | Mark alert as resolved |
| `GET` | `/api/health` | Device health/maintenance status |

---

## 8. Summary — How Java OOP Concepts Fit

```mermaid
mindmap
  root((SmartSphere OOP))
    Classes & Objects
      Device, Light, Fan, AC, DoorLock, SecurityCamera
      DeviceManager, AutomationEngine, EnergyMonitor
    Constructors
      Parameterized Device constructor
      super() calls in subclasses
    Inheritance
      Light/Fan/AC/DoorLock/Camera extend Device
    Interfaces
      Controllable — turnOn, turnOff, getStatus
      EnergyConsumer — getPowerUsage
    Dynamic Method Dispatch
      Device ref pointing to Light/Fan objects
      performAction resolved at runtime
    Packages
      devices, automation, energy, security, logging, exception
    Exception Handling
      Custom exceptions for invalid actions and thresholds
      try-catch in controllers
    Multithreading
      DeviceThread per device
      SecurityMonitorThread
      EnergyMonitorThread
    File Handling
      ActivityLogger writes to activity.log
      Optional sync to Supabase
```

> [!TIP]
> This architecture cleanly separates **presentation (Vercel)**, **business logic (Render/Java)**, and **persistence (Supabase)**, while ensuring every required Java OOP concept has a clear, demonstrable role in the system.
